    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="121"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2368½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">23 October, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Here is my idea of the form in
                    which we should submit our correspondence with Germany to the governments with
                    which we are associated as belligerents. What do you think of it? I dare say we
                    should send the correspondence to each of them as promptly as possible.<note
                        n="20" xml:id="d121fn1">For text of these notes as sent, see <ref
                            target="frus1918Supp01v01#pg_383">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, supp. 1, vol I, p.
                            383</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Faithfully Yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. W.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
